    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen im opening neovim, it cant read my init.lua, cannot create directory at /.local/state, and just says \"permission denied\", despite having the necessary permissions, even tried to 777 my home directory with chmod for experimenting, the same issue happens. Despite everything it opens, but with the default config.\n\ni apologize in advance if this turn out to be really easy to solve! \n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`nvim`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI would expect it to have permission to read and write to my home directory\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.10.4 e96f75a\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, 9.1.1165\n\n### Operating system/version\n\narchlinux 6.13.5-arch-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.39.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nInstalled from aur, arch repos and manually built from source",
